</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>  

<section id="section-1">
<title> Momentum of a system of particles </title>
<para id="element-12">The concept of linear momentum for a particle is extended to a system of particles by summing the momentum of individual particles. However, this sum is a vector sum of momentums. We need to either employ vector addition or equivalent component summation with appropriate sign convention as discussed earlier. Linear momentum of a system of particles is, thus, defined as :
</para>
<para id="element-14">
<definition id="definition-14"><term> Momentum of a system of particles  </term>
<meaning id="id8246461"> The linear momentum of a system of particles is the vector sum of linear momentums of individual particles.
</meaning>
</definition>
</para>
<para id="element-15">
<figure id="fig-15">
<title> Momentum of a system of particles </title>
<media id="id8246492" alt=""><image src="../../media/clm1.gif" mime-type="image/gif"/></media>
<caption> Particles moving with diferent velocities.</caption>
</figure>
</para>
<para id="element-16">
